The Berkeley "r" commands require exact case-sensitive matching of host
names because they are brain-damaged.  It's the same reason the /etc/hosts
based 4.2BSD "telnet" program required the case of the hostname to be an
exact match (that is, "telnet sri-nic.arpa" works, if that's the way it
looks in the /etc/hosts file, but "telnet SRI-NIC.ARPA" doesn't).

There really is no particularly good reason for it - I call it a bug.

--Pat.

